com.roche.iceboar.settings

Class GlobalSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.roche.iceboar.settings.GlobalSettings

  • public class GlobalSettings
extends Object
    This class defines properties that can be set in JNLP file to configure behaviour of Ice Boar application, ex. 
    <resources os="Windows" arch="x86">
 <property name="jnlp.IceBoar.targetJavaVersion" value="1.6.0_15"/>
 </resources>

      • JNLP_TARGET_JAVA_VERSION

        public static final String JNLP_TARGET_JAVA_VERSION
        "jnlp.IceBoar.targetJavaVersion"
        This property defines a Java (JRE) Version. In plain JNLP (when you do not use ice-boar) this is configured by <j2se> tag, key: version, ex:
        
 <resources os="Windows" arch="amd64">
 <j2se version="1.6+" ...>
        It is highly recommend to set this to version the same like in <j2se> tag - if user doesn't have Java installed in defined or newest version, then plain Java Web Start will download and install JRE in a version as specified (or newest).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_TARGET_JAVA_URL

        public static final String JNLP_TARGET_JAVA_URL
        "jnlp.IceBoar.targetJavaURL"
        This property defines a location of downloadable JRE ZIP file. The downloaded JRE must be in the same version as defined in JNLP_TARGET_JAVA_VERSION.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_JARS_PREFIX

        public static final String JNLP_JARS_PREFIX
        "jnlp.IceBoar.jar."
        This prefix is used to define properties that specify libraries needed. At least one dependency needs to be specified. In clear JNLP this properties correspond to:
        
 <jar href="guava-XX.X.jar"/>
 <jar href="slf4j-api-X.X.X.jar"/>
        You can't duplicate the property name. If you need to specify more than one entry, please create more properties that start from the same prefix e.g. 
        
 <property name="jnlp.IceBoar.jar.0" value="guava-XX.X.jar"/>
 <property name="jnlp.IceBoar.jar.1" value="slf4j-api-X.X.X.jar"/>
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_MAIN_CLASS

        public static final String JNLP_MAIN_CLASS
        "jnlp.IceBoar.main-class"
        This property defines the target main class. It is a actual code to be executed on a client machine and corresponds to the value of main-class property specified in <application-desc> tag, e.g.:
        
 <application-desc main-class="com.roche.MainClass">
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_INITIAL_HEAP_SIZE

        public static final String JNLP_INITIAL_HEAP_SIZE
        "jnlp.IceBoar.initial-heap-size" This property specifies an initial size of Java heap size to be used while executing the target application. It corresponds to initial-heap-size value in <j2se> tag, e.g.:
        
 <j2se href="..." initial-heap-size="128m"/>
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_MAX_HEAP_SIZE

        public static final String JNLP_MAX_HEAP_SIZE
        "jnlp.IceBoar.max-heap-size" This property define a max size of Java heap for target application. It correspond to max-heap-size value in <j2se> tag, e.g.:
        
 <j2se href="..." max-heap-size="1024m"/>
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_JAVA_VM_ARGS

        public static final String JNLP_JAVA_VM_ARGS
        "jnlp.IceBoar.java-vm-args" This property defines an additional set of standard and non-standard virtual machine arguments for the target application. It corresponds to java-vm-args value in <j2se> tag, e.g.:
        
 <j2se href="..." java-vm-args="-XX:+UseParallelGC"/>
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_CLOSE_ON_END

        public static final String JNLP_CLOSE_ON_END
        "jnlp.IceBoar.close-on-end" This property defines a behaviour after finishing staring a target application. When set on true, all Ice Boar windows will be close, when false windows will be NOT close. The second approach is useful for debugging. Default is set to true.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • JNLP_ICONS_PREFIX

        public static final String JNLP_ICONS_PREFIX
        "jnlp.IceBoar.icon."
        This prefix is used to define properties that specify icons for JFrame with progressbar. In clear JNLP this properties correspond to:
        
 <icon href="images/image.jpg"/>
        You can't duplicate the property name. If you need to specify more than one entry (e.g. for different sizes like 16x16, 32x32, 64x64, 128x128), please create more properties that start from the same prefix e.g. 
        
 <property name="jnlp.IceBoar.icon.0" value="images/icon-128x128.png"/>
 <property name="jnlp.IceBoar.icon.1" value="images/icon-64x64.png"/>
        Since:
        0.6
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
